    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The credibility assessment team concluded that the FEA modeling framework demonstrates High assurance for predicting compression-bending performance of the non-cannulated pedicle screw construct. Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 factors meet or exceed required levels; output comparison results satisfy all pre-established acceptance criteria. The shortfall in Test conditions (achieved level 1 vs. required level 3) was judged by the team to be offset by the strong quantitative agreement observed across all three QoIs and the conservative nature of the single-condition test protocol. The decision to accept the model at High assurance level is recorded.",
